Dreamed I was on top of a cliff, near the outskirts of town. It was after nightfall, train tracks running below, small house standing near the edge. I went to look at the horizon, late evening had rendered everything black, except a few rays coming behind mountains in distance

I went to the doorsill because it was open, inside a woman was writing mournful messages on cardboard and stacking them outside, on a balcony I hadn't seen. I asked her what happened, she said someone died - it was a literary character from a book called "The Reborn Unborn"

It was a highly spiritual text, I do not remember the content. It does not exist in real life, I checked. I recommended her to read the works of Julius Evola afterwards, to better be able to understand it (and no longer mourn). Outside it was dark, and snow had started falling.
